bqT pf-152_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-fivaXQ OAMge pf-151_">Currently, we only have one supplier which provides with Organic Pima Cotton fabric: <a href="https://bergmanrivera.com/" target="_blank">Bergman/Rivera</a>. This family-owned company is certified under Global Organic Textile Standard (GOTS), from the field to the finished garment. This certification not only guarantees the traceability of the Organic Pima Cotton, but also our standard of fair treatment to every person involved in the production chain. Their cotton production supports more than 160 Peruvian families, and all their products are made under Fair Trade standards.</span></p><p class="sc-DtmNo VpbqT pf-149_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-fivaXQ OAMge pf-148_"><a href="/pages/supply-chain" target="_self">Learn More About Our Supply Chain</a></span></p></div></div></div></div></div><div data-section-id="pf-cbb3" data-pf-type="Section" class="sc-itWPBs CnKWk pf-117_"><div style="--cw:1170px" class="sc-gHjyzD dqPPVt"><div class="sc-clIzBv iQyrr pf-118_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:6;--c-md:6;--c-lg:6"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-gnnDb bRALxe pf-119_"><div data-pf-type="Image" class="sc-ewSTlh klfUNH pf-120_"><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0550/2880/9974/t/8/assets/alpacas-1656962477528_1200x.jpeg?v=1656962480" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0550/2880/9974/t/8/assets/alpacas-1656962477528.jpeg?v=1656962480 1536w" width="3000" height="2000" sizes="(min-width: 1536px) 1536px, (min-width: 1024px) 1280px, (min-width: 640px) 768px, 320px" loading="lazy"/></div></div></div><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:6;--c-md:6;--c-lg:6"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-gnnDb bRALxe pf-121_"><h2 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-jlsrNB jrZWiU pf-122_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-fivaXQ OAMge pf-124_">Animals</span></h2><p class="sc-DtmNo VpbqT pf-125_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-fivaXQ OAMge pf-127_">We do not use any fur, leather, down/feathers, angora, and exotic animal skins.</span></p><p class="sc-DtmNo VpbqT pf-128_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-fivaXQ OAMge pf-130_">The only material of animal origin, that we plan to incorporate into our catalog in 2022 or 2023, is Royal Alpaca Wool, sourced from small Peruvian co-op farmers. All alpacas are non-mulesed, receive regular medical care, and roam free in the highlands in the Andes Mountains.</span></p><p class="sc-DtmNo VpbqT pf-131_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-fivaXQ OAMge pf-133_">We are committed to sourcing materials that do not compromise animals' wellbeing.</span></p></div></div></div></div></div><div data-section-id="pf-91d4" data-pf-type="GlobalSection" id="4ca000f2-ff50-4365-8916-3e0be11900c9" class="sc-cnHmbd gfqJIR pf-134_">{% capture content %}{% include 'pf-4ca000f2' %}{% endcapture %}
